.el .ds Aq '
.TH forge 1  "forge 1.0.0" 
.SH NAME
forge \- CLI toolkit for Reticulum mesh networks
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBforge\fR [\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR] [\fB\-q\fR|\fB\-\-quiet\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
CLI toolkit for Reticulum mesh networks
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Enable verbose logging
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Suppress all output except errors
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
forge\-init(1)
Initialize a new Reticulum network project
.TP
forge\-generate(1)
Generate interface configs for hardware
.TP
forge\-simulate(1)
Simulate a virtual Reticulum network
.TP
forge\-deploy(1)
Deploy configs to remote nodes
.TP
forge\-test(1)
Test network config, connectivity, and policies
.TP
forge\-monitor(1)
Real\-time network health dashboard (TUI)
.TP
forge\-completions(1)
Generate shell completions for bash, zsh, fish, or PowerShell
.TP
forge\-man(1)
Generate man page for forge
.TP
forge\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
.SH VERSION
v1.0.0
